What to change/ remove in which files?
- Variable names
- Database connection information
- Database tables setup

app.js
1. Session management - 
var PostgreSqlStore = new connectPgSimple({
  conString: "pg://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/[NameOfDatabase]",
  tableName: "NameOfTableInDatabaseToStoreSession",
  pruneSessionInterval: false,
});

var sessionOptions = {
  secret: "[Change secret key]",
  resave: false,
  saveUninitialized: false,
  store: PostgreSqlStore,
  cookie: { maxAge: 30 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000 } // 30 days
};

2. Change the saved favicon.ico file inside /public

db Folder
sessionTableSetup.sql
1. Run sessionTableSetup.sql to define the schema for the table to store sessions

index.js
var connectionString = process.env.DATABASE_URL || "pg://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/[NameOfDatabase]";
Change name of the variable that stores the connectionClient to the database {pintextDatabaseClient}

dbSetup.js
1. 
var connectionString = process.env.DATABASE_URL || "pg://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/[NameOfDatabase]";

2. Change name of the variable that stores the connectionClient to the database {pintextDatabaseClient}
3. Change the tables to be created and dropped and their corresponding schema. Divide the tables into primary and secondary depending upon their Foreign Keys and dependencies on other tables
Run dbSetup.js to setup the tables for your app

api/users Folder
passportLocalAuthentication.js
1. Change name of the variable that stores the connectionClient to the database {pintextDatabaseClient}
2. Change the name of the table and the record name in sqlQuery variables

users.js
1. Change name of the variable that stores the connectionClient to the database {pintextDatabaseClient}
2. Change the name of the table and the record name in sqlQuery variables